  Multiresolution analysis has applications across many disciplines in the
study of complex systems and their dynamics. Financial markets are among the
most complex entities in our environment, yet mainstream quantitative models
operate at predetermined scale, rely on linear correlation measures, and
struggle to recognize non-linear or causal structures. In this paper, we
combine neural networks known to capture non-linear associations with a
multiscale decomposition to facilitate a better understanding of financial
market data substructures. Quantization keeps our decompositions calibrated to
market at every scale. We illustrate our approach in the context of seven use
cases.
